ijk","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England"},"en":{"1520–1550":"1520–1550","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1546–1595":"1546–1595","1546":"1546","22 Jun 1546":"22 June 1546","1555":"1555","1520":"1520","1595":"1595","1550":"1550","3 Oct":"October 0003","1549":"1549","1516":"1516","Sheffield, Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barfield","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","(Suffolk, Rutland): of Norman origin, from Berville-la-Champagne in Eure, or from any of the six Bervilles in Normandy, three in Eure, two in Seine-Maritime, or one in Calvados (all France).","(Kent): variant of <b>Burvill</b>, a habitational name from Barville in Tilmanstone, Kent, named with Old English <i>bær</i> ‘bare’ + <i>feld</i> ‘open land’."],"variants":[{"name":"Barefield","meanings":["English (Oxfordshire and Berkshire): variant of   Barfield  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":29,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Barfield was born in 1520, in Shenfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with James Gedge. She died in 1550, in Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England, at the age of 30, and was buried in Barking, Essex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1520–1550":"1520–1550","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1546–1595":"1546–1595","1546":"1546","22 Jun 1546":"22. juuni 1546","1555":"1555","1520":"1520","1595":"1595","1550":"1550","3 Oct":"oktoober 0003","1549":"1549","1516":"1516","Sheffield, Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1520–1550":"1520–1550","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1546–1595":"1546–1595","1546":"1546","22 Jun 1546":"22. kesäkuuta 1546","1555":"1555","1520":"1520","1595":"1595","1550":"1550","3 Oct":"lokakuu 0003","1549":"1549","1516":"1516","Sheffield, Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1520–1550":"1520–1550","1516–1555":"1516–1555","1546–1595":"1546–1595","1546":"1546","22 Jun 1546":"22 juin 1546","1555":"1555","1520":"1520","1595":"1595","1550":"1550","3 Oct":"octobre 0003","1549":"1549","1516":"1516","Sheffield, Essex, England":"Shenfield, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Barking, Essex, England":"Barking, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Margaret Barfield est née en 1520, à Shenfield, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au mo